headline: The WSJ Dollar Index Rises 0.2% to 100.79
summary: 1435 GMT – Sterling is likely to continue rising gradually against the euro as U.K. growth outperforms the eurozone, Monex Europe analyst Nick Rees says in a note.  While U.K. growth is weak, it’s still marginally better compared to the eurozone, he says.  The U.K.’s less challenging policy environment and more limited political headwinds are also factors that could lead to sterling outperformance.
